Phyllis Latour Doyle should be made DBE for her services in regards to the liberation of France from Nazi occupied Germany, as well as a variety of other intelligence missions ahead of the D-Day landings.
A link to her story can be found here;

http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2846368/Former-British-wartime-spy-93-finally-recognised-liberating-France-Nazi-occupation-decades-spent-keeping-wartime-service-secret.html
